I have to clear up my work further a bit.

561
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,680
You’re going to go to bed very late, then

562
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,480
Please hold on a sec, P’Arthit.

563
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,520
Are you going to bed yet?

564
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:15,440
Here’s a hot cocoa for you.

565
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:16,680
Thank you.

566
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:21,440
I just got a reply from a company about the internship

567
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,480
So you have to be up for it.

568
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:24,240
Yes.

569
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:25,320
For how long?

570
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:27,080
A while, I guess.

571
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:27,760
Don’t go to bed too late, son.

572
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:29,240
I know

573
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:31,600
I’m going, then.

574
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:32,680
Thank you.

575
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:40,320
Hello, P’Arthit.

576
00:29:41,520 --> 00:29:42,880
P’Arthit krap.

577
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:45,280
Hello.

578
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:47,800
Hello.

579
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:16,520
Hey,

580
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:17,360
Mr. Sun.

581
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:18,800
Hey, Sawasdee krap, Khun Tod.

582
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:21,520
You can call me just Tod.

583
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:23,440
Okay.

584
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:32,520
Wait for me.

585
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:35,320
Sawasdee krap, P’Earth.

586
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:36,680
What’s the rush?

587
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:38,120
I have to talk to Khun Danai

588
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:39,160
He called for an urgent meeting.

589
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:41,640
He has to rush to the hospital.

590
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:44,960
I have to deliver this document too.

591
00:30:45,520 --> 00:30:46,480
What document?

592
00:30:46,640 --> 00:30:48,240
Do you want me to deliver it for you?

593
00:30:48,520 --> 00:30:50,240
It’s for Khun Paga

594
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:53,240
I can deliver it to her

595
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,760
Do you know Khun Paga at the Accounting Department?

596
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:59,680
Mr. Son can accompany me, right?

597
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:04,040
Yes, I can.

598
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:05,280
Okay.

599
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:07,000
Then, I leave it to you. Thank you so much

600
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:07,800
No problem.

601
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:08,800
It’s all my pleasure

602
00:31:09,080 --> 00:31:11,000
It’s all my pleasure too

603
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,000
What’s the matter?

604
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:22,480
Well, Khun Paga...we

605
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,520
have document to give it to you from the Procurement Dept

606
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:28,760
You are a new guy, right?

607
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:30,440
When you talk to a senior,

608
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:32,840
you must introduce who you are first.

609
00:31:33,080 --> 00:31:36,000
It’s not that I want to be nitpicking about these manners.

610
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:44,600
Sawasdee krap.

611
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:46,640
I’m Tod, Thanaphat Kengpaisarnpanich.

612
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:48,000
I’m from the Procurement Department.

613
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:49,240
It’s nice to meet you.

614
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:51,800
Hey, what are you doing?

615
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:53,560
What’s wrong with kids these days.

616
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:56,960
Who taught you to introduce yourself to a senior like that!!!

617
00:32:00,840 --> 00:32:02,480
“Kentpaisarnpanich”

618
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:04,680
What relationship do you have with P’Piroj.

619
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,720
He’s my uncle.

620
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:09,040
You are his nephew.

621
00:32:10,040 --> 00:32:11,840
How could you be like this?

622
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:14,200
How could you oversee anyone in the future?

623
00:32:16,520 --> 00:32:17,560
Yes.

624
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:20,040
Put down the document

625
00:32:20,600 --> 00:32:22,040
Put it here.

626
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:25,160
Please excuse us, Khun Paga

627
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:32,760
Mr. Son.

628
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:34,840
What did I do wrong in there?

629
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:36,320
I gave her a shakehand.

630
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,760
That’s common, right?

631
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:41,800
Guys.

632
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:45,520
There’s a new guy. His name is Nong Tod

633
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:48,840
He’s the nephew of Khun Piroj!!!!

634
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:52,320
SMH, I knew that already.

635
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:54,880
Som-O, you must get yourself close to him now

636
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:57,080
You could have a good future with him.

637
00:32:57,920 --> 00:33:00,360
He is so gorgeous like a roman god.

638
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:11,560
Wait. Nong Tod, Sawasdee ka

639
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:15,320
My name is Som-O. I’m the secretary in this department

640
00:33:15,800 --> 00:33:16,760
Do you understand Thai?

641
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:19,360
My name is P’Som-O like an orange O.

642
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:20,520
You mean “orange.”

643
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,080
Yes.

644
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:24,640
My seat is right here, Nong Tod.

645
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:27,080
And your seat is here.

646
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:29,800
Come to me if you need helps.

647
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:30,840
Got it.

648
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:33,720
Hey, Tod

649
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:37,680
I have assigns your tasks to Arthit.

650
00:33:37,880 --> 00:33:41,600
You can check with him. He’s been here for 4 months now

651
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:43,120
Thank you, P’Danai.

652
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:46,640
Everyone, please take care of Tod.

653
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:48,440
If you have anything, just ask them.

654
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:50,200
Okay, right?

655
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:52,840
Hey, bro

656
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:54,880
Nice to meet you.

657
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:59,680
Nice to meet you too.

658
00:34:07,080 --> 00:34:08,800
Here it is.

659
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:10,080
Microwaves….

660
00:34:10,160 --> 00:34:10,880
so it’s today

661
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:11,520
in the afternoon

662
00:34:11,600 --> 00:34:13,160
and again tomorrow.

663
00:34:13,880 --> 00:34:14,840
I got it.

664
00:34:17,240 --> 00:34:18,240
Arthit.

665
00:34:18,640 --> 00:34:19,120
Yes?

666
00:34:19,200 --> 00:34:20,400
Are you busy this afternoon?

667
00:34:21,160 --> 00:34:22,520
This afternoon?

668
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:24,360
I have to key in some info into the system.

669
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:25,400
Here’s the thing

670
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:29,080
P’Danai wants me to review the quality of products from the supplier.

671
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:31,680
I will go today and again tomorrow.

672
00:34:31,840 --> 00:34:33,560
I see that you came from the Production Department

673
00:34:33,680 --> 00:34:35,560
So you can be helpful to this process.

674
00:34:37,320 --> 00:34:39,240
I’m available tomorrow in the afternoon.

675
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:42,040
But today, I have to…

676
00:34:42,240 --> 00:34:43,840
You can go with her.

677
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:47,160
You want me to put in all of this info, right?

678
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:48,440
Yes

679
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:49,840
Okay.

680
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:51,000
Leave it to me.

681
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:52,920
Are you sure?

682
00:34:53,160 --> 00:34:54,440
Yes, I’m sure.

683
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:57,120
Okay.

684
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:58,320
Well then,

685
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:01,400
I put in all info in the first file before I go with her.

686
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:02,480
Okay.

687
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:05,120
Okay.

688
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,840
Hello, Kongpob.

689
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:17,040
I can’t hear you.

690
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:19,400
I just finished an interview for my internship

691
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:20,640
Where are you?

692
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:22,560
Kongpob,

693
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:25,280
I’m out to review products in a factory

694
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:27,440
Let’s talk via Line Messenger.

695
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:32,040
What did you say earlier?

696
00:35:32,440 --> 00:35:34,240
I just finished an interview for my internship

697
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:36,080
Are you free today?

698
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:41,800
I’m sorry.

699
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:42,680
It’s okay.

700
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:44,440
I didn’t look carefully either

701
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:49,040
I will get off my work late today.

702
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:50,760
I have to go to a factory in another area

703
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:51,880
What’s the matter?

704
00:35:52,080 --> 00:35:53,800
Can I go with you tomorrow?

705
00:35:54,040 --> 00:35:55,960
I want to see you when you are working

706
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:58,440
I can use it for my internship.

707
00:36:11,120 --> 00:36:12,120
Here.

708
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,080
Kongpob,

709
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:21,200
how long have you been here?

710
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:22,040
I’m sorry.

711
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:23,680
I got back home very late last night

712
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:24,840
It’s okay.

713
00:36:24,920 --> 00:36:26,440
I just got here too

714
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:33,320
P’Eart, Sawasdee krap.

715
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:34,080
I’m sorry.

716
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:35,080
Have I kept you waiting for me too long?

717
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:37,440
No, I just got here too.

718
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:40,160
Well, this is Kongpob.

719
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:42,080
The junior I told you that he wanted to see how we work

720
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:43,000
Sawasdee krap.

721
00:36:43,320 --> 00:36:44,040
Sawasdee ja.

722
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:45,120
I’m P’Earth.

723
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:48,040
If you have questions, you can ask me

724
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:49,720
Thank you, P’Earth.

725
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:50,760
All right, then. Get in the car.

726
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,480
There are many places we have to visit today

727
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:17,200
What’s wrong with it?

728
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:18,800
I got a flat tire.

729
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:20,480
Do you need a hand?

730
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:21,840
Don’t worry.

731
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:23,880
I can bring it to the garage myself.

732
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:26,000
Don’t you have a class to attend?

733
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:27,360
I do.

734
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:28,800
Leave it here.

735
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:29,720
You can get it fixed later.

736
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:30,760
Go to your class now.

737
00:37:32,120 --> 00:37:33,120
Okay.

738
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:42,320
Get on.

739
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:43,720
I’ll give you a ride.

740
00:37:48,240 --> 00:37:50,120
Is it going to be okay if I ride the pillion?

741
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:52,960
Are you going to get on it now

742
00:37:53,160 --> 00:37:54,840
or do you want to do the pushup first?

743
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:05,560
Are you ready?

744
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:07,120
Can I hold you?

745
00:38:08,320 --> 00:38:09,480
Then, get off.

746
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:00,320
Thank you, P’Arthit.

747
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:02,960
Do you like to ride a bicycle?

748
00:40:04,160 --> 00:40:04,880
Yes,

749
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,960
it doesn’t need fuel.

750
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,520
I can also get to exercise

751
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:11,560
Well then,

752
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:15,720
can I ride the pillion every now and then?

753
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:18,760
No.

754
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,120
Wait.

755
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:28,680
When does your class finish today?

756
00:40:30,280 --> 00:40:31,480
4 p.m.

757
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:34,000
Okay,

758
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:35,760
I’ll give you a ride, then.

759
00:40:40,040 --> 00:40:41,680
Now, go to your class.

760
00:40:52,640 --> 00:41:00,520
But I want to be an intern somewhere else.
I can get to learn new things
and apply them to our company.- Kongpob

761
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:02,200
You have slept?

762
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,040
Thank you.

763
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:13,240
Our company has accepted 2 interns.

764
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:14,760
You can call me Nai.

765
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:16,440
I’m from Chiangmai.

766
00:41:17,520 --> 00:41:19,560
Hey, that’s Nong Kong.

767
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:22,440
You didn’t tell me that he would do the internship here

768
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:25,560
I couldn’t find the right time to tell you

769
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:28,160
Normally, we can talk about anything, right?
